  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Frederick Douglass was violently removed from his seat in a railroad car by John A. Fisher, a lawyer from Harrisburg, Penn. At Harrisburg, William Lloyd Garrison was met by Dr. Rutherford and his sister-in-law Agnes Crain. Garrison is staying with Dr. Rutherford. Frederick Douglass is staying with Mr. Wolf, a colored friend. At the meeting in the court house, the large audience listened respectfully to Garrison. When Frederick Douglass rose to speak, there were yells of &quot;out with the damned nigger,&quot; and the mob outside made use of &quot;rotten eggs and brickbats, fire-crackers and other missiles.&quot; Garrison quieted the alarmed audience for a few moments.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The postscript is in the hand of another person and consists of this message: &quot;I am about leaving in the cars for Pittsburg[h] and I had to get a friend to close this Letter. WG We were well pleased with the visit of Your Husband to this place.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
